{"session_id":"svc-1778390960390993266","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-10T05:29:22.408664046Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"sonnet","sticky":{"key_present":true,"bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"requested_harness":"claude","resolved_harness":"claude","harness_source":"request_harness","requested_model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","resolved_model":"sonnet","work_dir":"/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-0ca4ffda-20260510T052914-d1f83d24","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead is too big when any of these holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate top-level deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across more than ~5 files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass and favor child-bead scoping before implementation.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children may split once more, and third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (focused title, description, AC; copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;` so the decomposition is visible.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260510T052914-d1f83d24/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing each child ID and slice, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a successful attempt. Do not mix partial implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260510T052914-d1f83d24/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;`.ddx/executions/20260510T052914-d1f83d24/no_changes_rationale.txt` must contain one:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` reject.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260510T052914-d1f83d24/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260510T052914-d1f83d24/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and project defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-0ca4ffda\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003elint: routinglint regression — run/try/work must not set Profile/Harness/Model\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;  The run/try/work dispatch paths must not set Profile, Harness, or Model directly on ResolvedConfig or Runtime structs — those are durable knobs that belong in config.LoadAndResolve. Without a mechanically-enforced lint rule, future edits can silently reintroduce the anti-pattern and bypass the fizeau routing contract.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE\u0026#xA;  cli/tools/lint/routinglint/analyzer.go (package routinglint) currently forbids retired compensating-routing identifiers (ResolveProfileLadder, ResolveTierModelRef, etc.) and flag literals (--escalate, profile_ladders). It does not yet forbid direct field assignment of Profile/Harness/Model on Runtime structs inside run/try/work command code paths. The SD-024 runtimelint analyzer (cli/tools/lint/runtimelint/analyzer.go:41) forbids durable-knob fields on *Runtime structs generically, but does not name a per-command allowlist or produce a test that verifies the run/work/try paths specifically. No TestRoutingLint* test exercises this invariant.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;  - Extend routinglint (cli/tools/lint/routinglint/analyzer.go) to flag direct Profile/Harness/Model field assignment on types matching *Runtime in cli/cmd/ run/work/try command files, or add a new rule in runtimelint covering this.\u0026#xA;  - Alternatively, add a targeted integration test TestRoutingLint_RunPathNeverSetsProfileDirectly that runs the analyzer against the live tree and asserts zero diagnostics for the assignment pattern.\u0026#xA;  - Fix any existing violations: cli/cmd/agent_cmd.go:1893-1897 passes overrides.Profile/Harness/Model through CLIOverrides to config.LoadAndResolve — verify this is compliant (CLIOverrides is not a Runtime struct).\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;  - Changes to agent_run or agent_run_overrides command behavior.\u0026#xA;  - Changes to the fizeau or ladder routing logic.\u0026#xA;  - Lint rules for non-routing fields on Runtime structs (covered by runtimelint).\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. cli/tools/lint/routinglint/ (package routinglint) contains the new rule or an integration test that enforces the Profile/Harness/Model-on-Runtime prohibition for run/try/work paths.\u0026#xA;2. TestRoutingLint_RunPathNeverSetsProfileDirectly in cli/tools/lint/routinglint/ (or a new integration test file): runs go run ./tools/lint/routinglint/cmd/routinglint ./... against the live tree and asserts zero violations for the run/try/work pattern.\u0026#xA;3. TestViolations (cli/tools/lint/routinglint/analyzer_test.go:12) still passes.\u0026#xA;4. TestClean (cli/tools/lint/routinglint/analyzer_test.go:21) still passes.\u0026#xA;5. cli/cmd/agent_cmd.go:1891-1897 CLIOverrides usage verified compliant (CLIOverrides is not a Runtime struct; no lint exemption needed).\u0026#xA;6. Any actual violations found in run/work/try paths are fixed or annotated with routinglint:legacy-rejection reason=\u0026#34;...\u0026#34;.\u0026#xA;7. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./tools/lint/routinglint/... green.\u0026#xA;8. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003cnotes\u003e\nGuardrail scope expanded by ddx-ae8787d7. Keep this bead only if it is folded into that broader lint plan or narrowed to a child; do not dispatch as the sole guardrail for the no-agent cleanup.\n    \u003c/notes\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:2, story:10, area:lint, kind:guardrail, reconciled:no-changes-state\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-e34994e2\" base-rev=\"8429fccfda19cd80d2d90887148e93f45bad65f8\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260510T052914-d1f83d24\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cnote\u003eNo governing references were pre-resolved. The bead description above is the primary contract. If it names files, specs, or prior beads, read those before editing. Ground decisions in what is already in the repository; do not guess.\u003c/note\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","attempt_id":"20260510T052914-d1f83d24","base_rev":"8429fccfda19cd80d2d90887148e93f45bad65f8","bead_id":"ddx-0ca4ffda","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260510T052914-d1f83d24","correlation_id":"ddx-0ca4ffda:20260510T052914-d1f83d24","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260510T052914-d1f83d24/prompt.md","prompt_sha":"4c933bcefc57e4d0ead83a7ee7f0d0b242949fcbf7f7b61a091ea6ccc7cf7a97","role":"implementer","session_id":"eb-68da4669","worker_id":""}}}
